OL,3,CCumbrian man embarks on virtual cycle
OL,4,Cto Mars in memory of his wife and
OL,5,Cdaughter
OL,7,FA Cumbrian man has embarked on a
OL,8,Fvirtual cycle to climb the highest
OL,9,Fmountain in our solar system in memory
OL,10,Fof his wife and daughter.
OL,12,F86-year-old Gerard McCarten is raising
OL,13,Ffunds for Hospice at Home as well as
OL,14,Fthe West Cumbria Society for the Blind
OL,15,Fand began his challenge at the start
OL,16,Fof October.
OL,18,FHe is hoping to have the challenge
OL,19,Fcompleted by mid-November where he
OL,20,Fwill finish at a local school in
OL,21,FWhitehaven.
